25/07/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- The government submitted an application Wednesday (23 July) to become a non-permanent member of the UN Security Council for a two-year term starting in 2009.
According to a statement issued Thursday by the foreign ministry, no decision will be made until 2008.
Turkey is one of the UN's founding members but has not been on the Security Council for 42 years.
In other news, Italy announced on Thursday that it would work to convince Turkey to co-operate with the peace process in Cyprus so that the island can enter the EU united in May 2004.
Italy holds the rotating EU presidency through the end of this year.
(Anadolu Agency, TRT 2, ANA, AFP - 24/07/03)
